(This is valid JSON: { "a" : 1 , "b" : 2 , "c" : 3 } This is invalid JSON: { "a" : 1 , "b" : 2 ,) Tj
T*
("c" : 3 , } The difference is the last comma. The JSON grammar specifies that a comma can) Tj
T*
(separate two members of an object but not postcede \("trail"\) a member. I think this was a) Tj
T*
