T*
(one after the "c" member. Here's what it would look like if trailing commas were permitted: { +) Tj
T*
("x": 0, "a": 1, "b": 2, "c": 3, + "y": 4, } It's the exact same text transformation regardless) Tj
T*
(of where we add the key. In the current model, we instead have this: { + "x": 0, "a": 1, "b":) Tj
T*
(2, - "c": 3 + "c": 3, + "y": 4 } Those are different transformations! Similarly if you want to) Tj
T*
(remove an element, you can't just delete the corresponding line 1 , you have to delete the line) Tj
